description: The Group Key Management cluster manages group keys for the node. The cluster is scoped to the node and is a singleton for the node. This cluster maintains a list of groups supported by the node. Each group list entry supports a single group, with a single group ID and single group key. Duplicate groups are not allowed in the list. Additions or removal of a group entry are performed via modifi­ cations of the list. Such modifications require Administer privilege.
